  "issue_number": 22,
  "issue_title": "beta: enforce tool-call gate (single chokepoint, per-origin ACLs, confirmation, rate limits)",
  "issue_body": "## Motivation\n\n`CoreConfig` already has `tool_policy` (allowed/denied by origin) and `actuation_safety` (confidence thresholds, multi-target rules) sections, but they're scaffolded \u2014 many code paths skip the gates or default to \"allow.\" For beta we want every tool call to pass through a single, consistently-enforced gate that the operator can audit and configure.\n\nToday's gaps observed in the codebase:\n- `handle_quick_tool_for_voice` dispatches some tools without consulting the tool policy.\n- `try_tool_call_with_context` accepts `confirmed: false` by default; nothing enforces a confirmation step for sensitive tools.\n- `ToolDispatcher` reads policy at startup but new tools loaded via skills aren't always re-checked against denied lists.\n- No per-tool rate limit (the config has `max_actions_per_minute_by_origin` but it's not wired to skill calls, only to direct actuation).\n- `RequestOrigin::Voice` vs `Telegram` vs `Api` is set at call sites but not consistently propagated through tool chains.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n- **Single chokepoint.** Every tool invocation \u2014 quick-tool, LLM-driven dispatch, skill execution, summary tools \u2014 flows through `ToolDispatcher::execute_with_gate(ctx, tool, args)`. No call sites bypass.\n- **Origin propagation.** `RequestOrigin` is required on `ToolExecutionContext`; remove all sites where it's silently defaulted.\n- **Per-tool ACLs.** `tool_policy.allowed_tools_by_origin` and `denied_tools_by_origin` are enforced at the gate. Wildcards (`*`) work for both origin and tool name. Deny rules override allow.\n- **Per-tool rate limits.** `max_actions_per_minute_by_origin` extended to also support per-tool: `max_actions_per_minute_by_tool = { play_media = 10 }`. Sliding window in the dispatcher.\n- **Confirmation flow.** Sensitive tools (configurable list: `requires_confirmation_tools`) must be invoked twice with the same args within a TTL window before they execute. First call returns a `ConfirmationPending` response with a stable token; second call within TTL passes `confirmed = true`.\n- **Skill-loaded tools.** When `skills/loader.rs` registers a new tool, run it through the policy check. Reject silently with an audit log entry if disallowed.\n- **Audit log.** Every gate decision (allow / deny / rate-limited / pending-confirmation) logged to the evidence trail (see related #).\n\n### Out of scope\n- Cryptographic signing of tool calls (deferred to evidence trail work).\n- Network/IO sandboxing of tool implementations themselves (deferred to sandbox policy work).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- A grep for `try_tool_call` / `ToolDispatcher::execute` finds zero callers that bypass the gate.\n- Setting `denied_tools_by_origin = { voice = [\"home_control\"] }` reliably blocks `home_control` from voice cycles, with a journal line explaining why.\n- Confirmation flow demonstrably works in a test: first call returns pending, second within TTL executes, second outside TTL errors.\n- Rate limits on a fast loop bounce off the limit after N calls.\n- A skill manifest declaring a permission not in `denied_permissions` loads; one declaring a denied permission is rejected.\n\n## Related\n\n- `CoreConfig.tool_policy`, `CoreConfig.actuation_safety`, `CoreConfig.skill_policy` \u2014 existing scaffolding.\n- Evidence-trail issue (filed alongside this one) \u2014 depends on this for the source of truth on gate decisions.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-02T09:29:19.000Z",
